  "text": "A multicenter study in which pretreatment of serum was incorporated into the assay reported sensitivity in urine of 100% (84 of 84) and serum of 94.2% (16 of 17). [CITATION_1] Results for all patients in whom urine and serum were tested for antigen between 2014 and 2018 and at least one urine or serum specimen type was positively analyzed. The serum was positive, but urine was negative in 17.3% (13 of 75) (unpublished, MiraVista Diagnostics). Both urine and serum should be tested for the highest sensitivity.",
